            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "If the plugin requires many floating windows. Then I think the authors of these plugins will do some encapsulation based on `nvim_open_win`. They simply pass a border or read the border from the plugin's configuration.  There are too many example plugins of doing this . like telescope lspsaga etc . implement it is not hard . but have this option  or not makes no difference to me.",
