            "body": "> They simply pass aborder or read the border from the plugin's configuration.\r\n\r\nExactly, but they should publicly make such an option available to the users (still a little of extra work more documentation to add etc), and from the user experience it is much much worse so for making borders look the same for every plugin should read every documentation how author called such option is it even available etc etc. And then pollute theirs configs with a lot of the same additional lines which just setting float border. Instead of setting one variable in one place.",
